    content: "&nbsp;\n<p id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1444744572842_11726\">AOM Day, which is celebrated annually on October 24th, is a national awareness day for Acupuncture an Oriental Medicine and is part of  a nationwide effort designed to increase public awareness of the progress, promise and benefits of Acupuncture and Oriental Medicine.</p>\n<p id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1444744572842_11737\">In honor of AOM Day we will be offering FREE  stress reduction MINI acupuncture treatments  <em>by appointment only</em> on Friday 10/23/15 from 1-4pm. Please join us, experience and learn more about acupuncture- the missing key to your health.</p>\n<p id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1444744572842_11738\">This MINI treatment can</p>\n\n<ul id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1444744572842_11713\">\n \t<li>lower stress</li>\n \t<li>alleviate anxiety</li>\n \t<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1444744572842_11712\">rejuvenate your body</li>\n \t<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1444744572842_11739\">relax your mind, and</li>\n \t<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1444744572842_11748\">stimulate your spirit</li>\n</ul>\n<p id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1444744572842_11749\">It only takes 15-20 minutes and uses powerful acupuncture points known to rebalance your body &amp; mind.</p>\n<p id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1444744572842_11740\">*C<strong>all to reserve your spot now &amp; bring a friend</strong>!</p>\n&nbsp;\n\nNot sure just how Acupuncture can benefit you? Check out this infographic:\n\n&nbsp;",
