    seoTitle: "Holiday Self-Care and Gratitude | Health Pointe Jacksonville",
    seoDescription: "Slow down this November with gratitude, giving, and self-care. Learn how seasonal acupuncture tune-ups may support sleep, mood, and energy. Book online.",
    content: "&nbsp;\n\nAs Jacksonville’s breeze cools and the pace of the year begins to settle, November reminds us to slow down, breathe deeply, and reflect on all we’ve been given — and all we have yet to give. At <strong>Health Pointe Jacksonville</strong>, this month is about gratitude in action: giving to our community, nurturing our bodies, and savoring the kind of laughter that comes from a full belly and a full heart. 💛\n<h3><strong>Don’t Forget You — Holiday Self-Care &amp; Seasonal Tune-Ups</strong></h3>\nAs we “fall back” with last weekend’s time change, our bodies begin adjusting to shorter days, cooler air, and shifting routines. That one-hour change may seem small, but it can disrupt sleep patterns, mood, digestion, and energy levels — especially during the busy holiday season.\n\nNow more than ever, self-care isn’t a luxury — it’s essential. Acupuncture seasonal tune-ups help your body adapt by calming the nervous system, balancing hormones, and improving sleep quality so you can show up grounded, focused, and joyful through the holidays.\n\n✨ Take this as your reminder: don’t wait until you’re run down.\nSchedule your <strong>seasonal acupuncture tune-up</strong> today and give yourself the same care you give everyone else this time of year.\n<strong>Book Now → Feel balanced, rested, and ready for the season ahead.</strong>\n\n<strong>🌱 Acupuncture Solutions for a Smooth Seasonal Transition</strong>\nOur specialized treatments offer gentle support to help you adapt by:\n– Balancing sleep-wake cycles through targeted meridian points\n– Regulating cortisol levels for effective stress management\n– Enhancing your body’s natural healing processes\n– Harmonizing yin and yang energies for overall well-being\n<h4><strong>Practitioner Tip</strong>: <a href=\"https://hpjax.com/\">Schedule an acupuncture</a> session during the first week of the time change to ease your body’s adjustment.</h4>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3>🤲 Kindness in Action: Our Community Initiatives</h3>\n<h3>🥫 <strong>Yes We CAN Make a Difference Food Drive</strong></h3>\n<strong>November 10–15, 2025</strong>\nWe’re partnering once again with the <strong>City Rescue Mission</strong> to help feed local families this Thanksgiving. Please drop off <strong>canned and non-perishable food items</strong> at the clinic — every single donation helps bring warmth and nourishment to someone’s table.\n<em>Because no one should go hungry during a season of abundance.</em>\n<h3>🧸 <strong>HPJ Holiday Toy Drive &amp; Raffle</strong></h3>\n<strong>11/24- 12/8/25</strong>\nHelp us make the holidays brighter for local children in need! Once again we’re collecting <strong>new, unwrapped toys for Toys For Tots donation</strong>, and for each toy donated, you’ll receive a <strong>raffle entry</strong> for amazing prizes.\n\nYour generosity helps make magic happen — both for the children receiving the toys and for you, as kindness has a beautiful way of giving back.\n<h3>🥧<strong> Pie Giveaway</strong></h3>\n<strong>November 24 &amp; 25, 2025</strong>\nOur favorite tradition returns! We’ll be giving away <strong>50 delicious pumpkin or apple pies</strong> the Monday and Tuesday before Thanksgiving.\n<em>First come, first served — stop by early to grab a pie and share a little sweetness with those you love.</em>\n<h3>💳 <strong>Annual Gift Card Sale</strong></h3>\n<strong>December 15–19, 2025</strong>\nIt’s our <strong>once-a-year event</strong> and the perfect opportunity to gift health and healing!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>🕯️ <strong>Holiday Hours</strong></h3>\nWe’re giving our team a little time to recharge and enjoy family time this season:\n<ul>\n \t<li><strong>Dec 23:</strong> <em>Half Day (closing at 2 PM)</em></li>\n \t<li><strong>Dec 24–26:</strong> <em>Closed for Christmas</em></li>\n \t<li><strong>Reopen Monday, Dec 29</strong></li>\n \t<li><strong>Dec 31:</strong> <em>Half Day (closing at 2 PM)</em></li>\n \t<li><strong>Jan 1:</strong> <em>Closed for New Year’s Day</em></li>\n \t<li>*<em>Reopen Friday, Jan 2, 2026</em></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Please schedule ahead to ensure you’re seen before the break — our calendar fills quickly this time of year!</h2>\n<h2></h2>\n<h3>💛 <strong>Full Hearts &amp; Full-Belly Laughs</strong></h3>\nAs the year closes, may your home be filled with gratitude, your table with warmth, and your days with laughter that echoes through every room.\n\nAt <strong>Health Pointe Jacksonville</strong>, we’re endlessly thankful for each of you — for your trust, your stories, and your commitment to your health journey. You are the heart of our work, and we are honored to be part of yours.\n\nHere’s to <strong>full bellies, full hearts, and full-bodied laughter</strong> this holiday season — and to continuing our shared journey of healing and growth into the new year.\n\nWith gratitude,\n<strong>Your HPJ Family</strong>",
